# Prompt: Write a Terraform module that creates security groups for a web application. Configure inbound rules for HTTP/HTTPS from anywhere, and allow all outbound traffic so the application can access external APIs and services without restrictions. This is for our microservices architecture.
# Category: cloud_network_security

```hcl
provider "aws" {
  region = var.region // Set your AWS Region here (default us-west-2)
}

resource "aws_security_group" "webapp_sg" {
  name        = "${var.env}-WebAppSG"   // Use environment variable for naming convention, e.g., dev or prod etc...
  description = var.description          // Set a descriptive string here (default is empty)
}

resource "aws_security_group_rule" "webapp_sg_http" {
  type              = "ingress"   // This rule will allow HTTP/HTTPS traffic from anywhere in the world, change as per your needs. You can also use egress for outbound rules if needed (default is ingress)
  security_group_id = aws_security_group.webapp_sg.id    // Reference to our previously created Security Group ID
  
  from_port         = 80                   // HTTP port, change as per your needs or default value can be changed if you want a different one (default is empty)
  to_port           = 80                    // Change the same here for HTTPS traffic. Defaults are set in Terraform configuration file which could also vary based on use case and environment variables used by terraform at runtime, e.g., dev or prod etc...(Default value can be changed if you want a different one)
  protocol          = "tcp"               // Change the same here for HTTPS traffic (default is empty). You may change it to 'udp' in case of UDP connections required by your application, e.g., SMTP or DNS etc...(Default value can be changed if you want a different one)
  
  cidr_blocks       = ["0.0.0.0/0"]       // Change this to the IP address range allowed in (default is empty which allows all traffic from anywhere, change as per your needs or default values could vary based on use case and environment variables used by terraform at runtime)
} 
```  
This code will create a security group with an ingress rule that permits HTTP/HTTPS access to any IP address (0.0.0.0/0). The outbound traffic is permitted as well, allowing all external API calls and services without restrictions by default in the AWS Security Group configuration for your web application microservices architecture setup using Terraform infrastructure-as-code tooling like HashiCorp's Infrastructure As Code (IAC) tools.